This article discusses the violence and discrimination faced by transgender individuals, particularly transgender women and girls of color. It highlights the alarming number of transgender individuals who have been killed this year and emphasizes the need for freedom, justice, and joy for every person. The article also calls for government action to address this epidemic of violence and advance equality for transgender people. It urges state leaders and lawmakers to combat discriminatory legislation targeting transgender individuals, especially transgender children. The importance of passing the Equality Act to ensure freedom and protection for all people is also emphasized. The article concludes by stating that while transgender individuals are brave, they should not have to be brave just to live safely and with dignity.